About this item

  • Sound Quality: Truly immerse yourself in your games with hardware-driven virtual 7.1 surround sound for precisely located audio. Inline Remote :Yes
  • Microphone: Redgear Cosmo 7.1 comes equipped with a high quality built-in noise cancelling microphone for a quick and stable communication
  • Build Quality: Its luxurious noise-isolating memory foam ear pads and adjustable split headband which reduces pressure and provides optimal comfort for long gaming sessions
  • Noise Cancellation: Redgear Cosmo 7.1 provides you a passive noise cancelling experience. Its closed earcups design blocks any kind of distraction from outside which helps you keep focus during the game for as long as you want
  • Other Features: This headset has an amazing RGB LED light effect on ear-ups and tip of the microphone. It also comes equipped with audio control which helps control volume

    How are ratings calculated?
    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Amaan Ahmed
    5.0 out of 5 stars Read Before buying it ( Especially mobile users !!)
    Reviewed in India on 26 May 2020
    Colour: BlackPattern name: Gaming HeadphoneVerified Purchase
    One of the best Gaming headphones i ever bought ! Seriously few words can't describe the goodness of this beast. So here's my review. I'm a gamer ( pc & mobile ) and my experience with redgear isn't very good until i bought this. Previously i was using a redgear cloak which stopped working after 7 months of purchase ( still waiting for the replacement ! ). I need a headphone badly but I was confused with Various product like Eksa e3000 , redgear Cosmo , redgear thunder , cosmic byte europa equinox and so on. I mostly use my headphones with mobile that's why I was hesitating to buy a usb headphone. I almost went for eksa but eventually i found there's no service center of eksa anywhere in India. Then i gambled my money for Redgear Cosmo 7.1 as i was not sure it'll work with phone as some people say mic will not work with phones and all. But then it got delivered and i was quite afraid it will not work then I'm effed up. I plug it into phone ( with the help of OTG ofcourse ) and o boy , o boy it is working fantabulously. Audio quality is damn good and the mic is love. Everything about the headphones is awesome from build quality of body and wire to amazing RGB. And the controller is freaking awesome especially with the white backlight. Now let me clear the doubts of new buyers ( especially for mobile users ) it'll work with every smartphone "BUT" the mic won't work with phones who have a seperate 3.5 audio jack. As there's no connectivity of mic through charging port. But good for phone users like OnePlus and all type c Audio jack mobile phone it'll work absolutely perfect , you just need a good quality OTG adapter. The downside of this headphone is its more battery consuming as it runs on a USB ( Digital connectivity , 3.5 mm jack has analogue connectivity). Although i prefer this headphones for mostly gaming and lil bit of music. Thanks for reading my review !

    This is an awesome product, and the bass is toooo good. Its been 3years and it works perfect. I play cs go, valorant, apex its truly awesome. As im active on discord the noise cancellation works perfect even with the TV on behind me.
    There is something i want to help you guys with.
    In windows 10, you may notice a bug when device is connected but gives you error anc even does not work when connected.
    Dont worry, its because of the secure boot which verifies the driver signature blah bhal bhal.

    Fix: before booting pc go to boot settings.-->then disable secure boot.

    Thats it.
    Apart from this everything will work fine.
